<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Barbarians are the same way...</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Erik the Red, UDL">Erik the Red, UDL</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 1:00 p.m. 18/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Barbarians are the same way...<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1534" TARGET=_self>Answer, please disregard above post.</A> (Ceyana)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>We police our own. Very seldom do you here about some Barb killing within his own race. If it happens, a simple /shout or /ooc to the Everfrost Peaks zone and the Halas zone will warn everyone and mark that killer for what he/she is. Anyone who gets marked has pretty rough going from then on. They are hunted by the other players and they wont receive any help with groupings/heals.

<P>--Erik the Red, UDL
<P>Its NOTHING like the Abyss server of UO. In fact, IMO, I find the non-PvP servers to be more "DeWdIsH" than the PvP server.
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
